cs.LO, cs.LT, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces an extension of a temporal logic and investigates its properties and decision problems. 
- cs.LT (Automata and Formal Languages) is also likely as the paper uses automata-theoretic approach in solving the satisfiability problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as temporal logic is often used in formal system design and verification, which is related to programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as temporal logic is used in reasoning about actions and planning in AI. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also possible as the paper deals with an extension of a formal language (temporal logic) and its decision problems.
